args:
Another Styx explains that the discord between
Catherine and Eugene is the cause of the
recent disturbances. The pair tries to reconcile,
but the surface-level nature of it does not
work with the Styxes, who continue to sow
increasing amounts of chaos.
No good. We can't find it anywhere.
Say, where are Mym and the others?\nWe were supposed to meet them here.
Prince, you must come to the restaurant\nacross the way! Mym has... She's...\nLook, please just come! It's terrible!
Mym, you need to slow down! You too,\nSam. Surely milk won't fix whatever\nyou're feeling!
Even a dragon needs to wallow in her\nsorrows sometimes. Milk and tears\nand a dragon's yearning...
Yeah, what she said! Now you listen up.\nAre you listening? Good. 'Cause you\nknow my darling? He's SO nice and kind!
But sometimes I just want him to maybe...\nI dunno. Yell at me more? Is that weird?\nAm I being selfish?

Love based on nothing but kindness
is faerie-tale, picket-fence business.
Real love is about accepting each other's
flaws and coming out with bruised hearts.
So what are you saying?\nOur love is only getting started?\nIS THAT WHAT YOU'RE SAYING?!
Mym, are you all right? I heard you\nwere in trouble.
Oh, she's fine. She just got to talking with\nSam and the hostess here, and, well...\nI guess she got a little carried away.
Sam seems a bit sulky, but otherwise\nappears to be all right.
Ugh, how embarassing. Here we are in a\ncrisis, and I'm sitting around drinking milk.\nMILK, of all things!
You should scold me for acting like this!\nCome on, do it! Really let me have it!\nGIMME ALL YA GOT!
This really isn't the time for...uh...\nwhatever it is you want here.

Do it already! You humans only live for,
like, a year or something, so we need
to fight it out here and now and deepen
our love! So get to figh—ACK!

Fighting... That's it! I remembered!
I remembered the word you're absolutely
not supposed to say in front of one
of these immature Styx!
She's right—and that means it was the\ntwo of you who started this whole mess.

The ugliness of your squabbling created a
bad view of humanity in your original Sam,
and that became the seed from which all
the naughty copies sprung.

That's why Sam fled the house. But if the
two of you can patch up your relationship,
I imagine the bad image it has of people
will be dispelled.
You were trying to get us to make up...
But when all that effort came to nothing,\nanyone'd want a shoulder to cry on.
Okay, awesome, excellent narration.\nSo how do we get all the other Styxes\nto stop running around causing trouble?
The pranks and the milk-drinking come\nfrom the same place: A desire to forget\nhow unbearable things are.
...I don't even remotely think what I said\nyesterday was uncalled for.
However, I also realize things cannot\nsimply continue on as they are.

Regardless of intentions, I upset Sam—
and more importantly, I'd like to put this
awkward mood with Eugene behind me.
So with that in mind...
H-hold out your hand, Eugene!\nWe shall shake and make up!
Catherine, you really know how to push\nmy buttons.
But I feel the same as you do. I've been\nantsy and uncomfortable since yesterday.
So yeah. Let's shake on it.\n...Oh, gross. You're all sweaty.
Honestly, you have no delicacy at all!\nYour hand is no less so!
Sorry, Sam. ...That we're like this, I mean.

*sniff* Dear me, I'm going to tear up.
Well then, this should be enough for
the other Styxes' hearts to be cleansed,
which meeeeans...
NOTHING! It means absolutely NOTHING!\nKya ha ha ha! Oh, but you really are\na naive bunch of saps!
This mealymouthed, skin-deep type\nof reconciliation won't do squat for\nthe Styxes.

It's shallow and you know it! Something
still lurks in the depths of your
consciousness, and so long
as it remains there... Hmph!
So here's a little thank-you present\nfor showing us how much you suck:\nWe'll rip you to pieces if we find you!
The Styxes are multiplying at a furious\nrate, and getting more violent to boot!\nI fear our town may not survive.
Never mind the town—I'm more worried\nabout the entire CONTINENT.
Guys, try shaking hands again!\nMaybe you need to do it harder!
Yeah, apparently there's something\n＂lurking in our consciousness,＂ but I\nhave no idea what that even means!
You there, the lost and confused ones.\nPlease come this way.
Talk can take place later.\nThe prudent course now is escape.
